ENTRY       EC 2.1.1.154                Enzyme
NAME        isoliquiritigenin 2'-O-methyltransferase;
            chalcone OMT;
            CHMT
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring one-carbon groups;
            Methyltransferases
SYSNAME     S-adenosyl-L-methionine:isoliquiritigenin 2'-O-methyltransferase
REACTION    S-adenosyl-L-methionine + isoliquiritigenin = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 2'-O-methylisoliquiritigenin [RN:R07242]
ALL_REAC    R07242
SUBSTRATE   S-adenosyl-L-methionine [CPD:C00019];
            isoliquiritigenin [CPD:C08650]
PRODUCT     S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine [CPD:C00021];
            2'-O-methylisoliquiritigenin [CPD:C15531]
COMMENT     Not identical to EC 2.1.1.65, licodione 2'-O-methyltransferase [2]. While EC 2.1.1.154, isoliquiritigenin 2'-O-methyltransferase can use licodione as a substrate, EC 2.1.1.65 cannot use isoliquiritigenin as a substrate.
